'''Project1.pyAuthor: Abraham ReinesDate: May 21, 2023Modified: May 21, 2023Description:This program asks the user to input a 2-digit number and then prints out the digits three times. It also incorporates additional functionality:1. Asks the user to enter a 3-digit number and then prints out those digits twice.2. Asks the user to enter a 5-digit number and then prints out those digits twice.3. Prints "This Program Was Written by AJR".'''# Prompt the user and get the input for a 2 digit numberNum2Dig = int(input('Enter a 2 digit number: '))# Compute the result for a 2 digit numberResult2Dig = Num2Dig * (3*7*13*37)# Print the result for a 2 digit numberprint('Digits repeat three times:', Result2Dig)# Prompt the user and get the input for a 3 digit numberNum3Dig = int(input('Enter a 3 digit number: '))# Compute the result for a 3 digit numberResult3Dig = Num3Dig * (7*11*13)# Print the result for a 3 digit numberprint('Digits repeat twice:', Result3Dig)# Prompt the user and get the input for a 5 digit numberNum5Dig = int(input('Enter a 5 digit number: '))# Compute the result for a 5 digit numberResult5Dig = Num5Dig * (11*9091)# Print the result for a 5 digit numberprint('Digits repeat twice:', Result5Dig)# Print the program author's nameprint('This Program Was Written by AJR')# Warning'''Please note this program does not include error checking for input validation. Ensure that the correct number of digits is entered.'''